results.name: Number of series-reduced rooted identity trees whose leaves span an initial interval of positive integers with multiplicities the integer partition with Heinz number n.
comment: A rooted tree is series-reduced if every non-leaf node has at least two branches. It is an identity tree if no branch appears multiple times under the same root.
The Heinz number of an integer partition (y_1,...,y_k) is prime(y_1)*...*prime(y_k).
